The judge who gave the go-ahead had been appointed by former President Donald Trump.Missouri Attorney General Eric Schmitt and Louisiana Attorney General Jeff Landry sought the deposition for a free speech case filed in May. The pair has alleged the Biden administration collaborated with Big Tech to quell speech about COVID-19, election integrity, and other topics unfairly.Psaki had stoked ire from conservatives last year when she claimed at the White House podium that the administration was "flagging problematic posts for Facebook that spread disinformation." Geoengineering - White House proposes blocking sunlight to fight global warming: What Could Possibly Go Wrong?
American Thinker ^ | 11/19/2022 | Eric Utter
https://www.americanthinker.com/blog/2022/11/white_house_proposes_blocking_sunlight_to_fight_global_warming.html

The White House recently announced that it was funding a five-year research plan for a controversial proposal to fight climate change by geoengineering â i.e., technologies and processes that can be used to artificially modify the Earth's climate.

This research would be dedicated specifically to a form of geoengineering known as "solar radiation management," which involves spraying fine aerosols into the atmosphere to reflect sunlight away from the Earth. The hope is that, once the sunlight is reflected, less heat will be generated, and ergo temperatures will go down. Presto: actual anthropogenic climate change! A global SPF 100, as it were!

The research reportedly will attempt to model how solar radiation management might impact the atmosphere, as well as assess its viability as a potential technique to be employed to "manage near-term climate risk."

They're hoping to fight the scourge of climate change by blindly trying to change the climate? What is it with Democrats? They're also fighting racism with racial quotas and making race the primary consideration in, well, everything. That's working well, isn't it? Next, they'll propose fighting drug abuse by giving out free needles and crack pipes. Oh wait, they're already doing that. Why haven't they yet suggested we combat STDs by having indiscriminate sex with as many other people as possible?

Now they're going to "cancel" the sun, without which life on Earth would be impossible? What could go wrong?!

And would this be a unilateral decision? "Hope the rest of you guys don't mind, but we're blocking the sun! Oops, we didn't expect that! Our bad. Sorry, might be a bit chillier than we'd like for a while!"

Saudi Arabiaâs Dar Al Arkan real estate company has signed a deal with the Trump Organization to develop a signature Trump Resort worth $4 billion in Muscat, Oman.

The 100-meter-high hilltop development is set to be one of the worldâs largest mixed-use real estate projects, situated directly by the sea, the company said in a statement on Sunday.

The AIDA project, a joint venture with the Oman Tourism Development Company (OMRAN Group), will include residential villas, a hotel, and a golf course built near Muscat.

Development of the project will begin next year and is expected take more than a decade to complete.

âWhen we were looking at our next project and where we wanted to expand our footprint, we knew it had to be in an outstanding location and with an amazing team,â Eric Trump, Executive Vice President of the Trump Organization, said in a statement.

âAt AIDA, in the heart of Muscat, Oman situated directly overlooking the incredible sea, we have truly found that. Together with Dar Al Arkan, we are going to deliver an exceptional Trump Golf resort with the finest residential villas, a world-class hotel, and an iconic golf course, all in one of the most beautiful settings,â Trump added.

AIDAâs master plan was designed to adopt architectural foundations, utilizing Omanâs rich natural surroundings. It is being developed sustainably, fully respecting and preserving the topography and unique environmental features of the area with homes integrating seamlessly within the cliffs.

âThe Trump Organization is known for its exclusive, world-class developments. Superior quality, detail, and perfection are the standards that Trump demands throughout its projects â from residential to resort, from hotel to golf, and from commercial office to retail,â said Dar Al Arkan Chairman Yousef al-Shelash.

âWe are always looking to enhance Dar Al Arkanâs unique projects with premium facilities and experiences, and our partnership with Trump will distinguish our first project in Oman and put it on the global map.â

The new Trump property, which will feature a championship golf course designed by a renowned golf professional, will be built upon a hill with sweeping views of the sea.

The meticulously planned golf course will include state-of-the-art golf facilities, an expansive golf club, and an array of amenities ultimately creating a new luxury benchmark for golf in the region.

âAIDA sits on a high peak overlooking one of the most breath-taking horizons in the world. Imagine the beautiful setting of a villa in these majestic surroundings or playing a game of golf overlooking the sea â it is truly unrivalled,â said Dar Al Arkan Globalâs CEO Zaid el-Chaar.

HOW TO FIX VOTING.
1. arrive at the neighborhood precinct home with the garage door open. sign outside says "Vote Here".
2. walk up to the table and sign the poll book with an ID to get your ballot.
3. go to the private booth, fill out your ballot ( that has a unique serial number) and then tear off the stub with the matching serial number.
4. drop your ballot into the sealed box.
5. when 8pm arrives... all persons in line get a reservation to complete their vote. anyone arriving after 8pm, are turned around. vote by 8 or its too late.
6. every neighborhood has a precinct, so that the number of ballots handed out, matches the number of ballots counted.
7. the count begins after tha last person in line votes.
8. the totals are certified right then and there for that precinct with three copies of the certification, and the totals are phoned in to HQ and emailed to HQ as needed.
9. the ballots are scanned into a public facing website for people to type in their unique serial number, and view their ballot.
10. only the voter knows his serial number and how he voted. this makes auditing cost free, and provides assurance that the ballots are not tampered with.
the machine ballot scanner is used after the election is counted by hand. hand counts determine results, scanned images are only for record keeping purposes and full transparency. any person can type in a serial number, and view a ballot...no big deal election is over.
11. any problems reported to a toll free auditing number, excessive issues fixed immediately, those ballots and their images held for 24 months in archive or longer.???
12. results are called in ( over pa system, conferencing speaker etc), to a room with a tote board, and all observers in the room watch and hear the totals coming in while standing in the room, in each county election HQ.
13. the state SOS HQ gets the final totals, via zoom call and posts them in real time to the SOS webpage and the media outlets get the totals from there.
no more edison system, no more EMS, no more voter database ERIC,
the only SOS database that exists is each county has a record of your name address etc, voter registration info, to put you into the poll book at each precinct.
14. you must be in the system at least 1 month before the election, no same day registrations. no ballot given without an ID. to verify registration, pool book entry. no ballot given without a signature in person.
15. NO MORE MAIL IN VOTING. ONLY GET A BALLOT THAT DAY, IN PERSON.
16. there will be enough ballots because we have a cutoff of 1 month before the election to prepare the precinct pollbooks, and we know how any people are registered in total for that polling location.
